snippet.textDisplay: You’ll find many Muslims have names of Allah’s 99 attributes. So for example names like: Rahman, Kabir, Malik, Majid etc. But Muslims place Abdul before these names. Abdul means “servant of” which then follows the name of Allah (eg. Abdul Rahman - the servant of The Most Merciful).
